sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: S-tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a S-tag head domain designed to be at the N-terminus of a protein. S-tags are a type of affinity tag that can be used to purify and/or measure the quantity of proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This head domain begins with Met-Lys to promote efficient translation of the protein in ''E. coli''.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K392005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tadashi Nakamura, Shuhei Yasumoto, Takahiro Saka, Saya Kakuda
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: LacI promoter with RBS, followed by OmpA outer membrane protein and linker for Escherichia coli cell surface display.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Composite part BBa_K392001 (LacI promoter + RBS) and registry part BBa_K103006 (OmpA w/ linker).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: HA tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a HA tag head domain designed to be at the N-terminus of a protein. HA tags are a type of affinity tag that can be used to purify and/or measure the quantity of proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This domain encodes the HA sequence YPYDVPDYA. The codons at each amino acid position were selected to avoid rare codons as much as possible in organisms like ''E. coli'', humans, mouse, ''B. subtilis'', ''C. elegans'', ''Streptomyces coelicolor'' and other common model organisms and/or industrial hosts. Another factor in codon selection was avoiding avoid repeat sequences.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: S
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bing Xia
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This S-tag can be added between two protein parts. ---- This part is in BBb Format. It is flanked by BamHI and BglII sites instead of XbaI and SpeI. More information about the BBb Format is available at:
[http://openwetware.org/wiki/Template:AndersonLab:BBb_Standard BBb Standard Description Page]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
Construction of S-tag> basic part K112705

Sub into pBca1256                      (EcoRI/BamHI, 2472+47, L)
Product is pBca1256-K112705
-----------------------------------------------
dv013	Forward Biobricking of S-Tag>
cgataGAATTCatgAGATCTatgaaagaaaccgctgctgctaaattcg
dv014   Reverse Biobricking of S-Tag>
cgttaGGATCCgctgtccatgtgctggcgttcgaatttagcagcagcgg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Met-His
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jerneja Mori
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: His-tag with amino acid Methionine.His-tag is used for detection of His-tagged proteins by anti-His antibodies.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Part was constructed by primer annealing.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: c-Myc
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anja Korenčič
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: c-myc tag is used for detection of proteins by anti-c-myc antibodies.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Gene was designed to be constructed by primer annealing. Includes start codone.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ErbB1 (SP)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: EGFR/ErbB1 signal peptide; mediates protein transport to a translocational pore
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Freiburg 2008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The N-terminal signal-peptide ensures protein transport to the cytoplasm-membrane.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Part derived from the sequence of EGFR/ErbB1

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Strep-tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a Strep tag head domain designed to be at the N-terminus of a protein. Strep tags are typically used for detection, purification and immobilization of proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This domain encodes the Strep tag sequence WRHPQFGG. The codons at each amino acid position were selected to avoid rare codons as much as possible in organisms like E. coli, humans, mouse, B. subtilis, C. elegans, Streptomyces coelicolor and other common model organisms and/or industrial hosts. Another factor in codon selection was avoiding avoid repeat sequences.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: HA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anja Korenčič
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: HA-tag is used for detection of HA-tagged proteins by anti-HA antibodies.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Gene was designed to be constructed by primer annealing. Includes start codon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Part was constructed by primer annealing.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1909003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: EnvZ Signal Peptide and first Transmembrane Domain
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel Wedemeyer
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: For EnvZ fusion protein design. Long description will be added soon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Source: E. coli EnvZ protein (ncbi: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/947272)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: V5 tag
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a V5 epitope tag head domain designed to be at the N-terminus of a protein. V5 tags are a type of epitope tag that can be used to measure the quantity of proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This head domain begins with Met-Lys to promote efficient translation of the protein in E. coli. Rare codons from various model organisms were avoided where possible.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: c-Myc
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a c-Myc tag head domain designed to be at the N-terminus of a protein. c-Myc tags are a type of affinity tag that can be used to purify and/or measure the quantity of proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This tail domain encodes the c-Myc sequence EQKLISEEDL. The codons at each amino acid position were selected to avoid rare codons in organisms like ''E. coli'', humans, mouse, ''B. subtilis'', ''C. elegans'', ''Streptomyces coelicolor'' and other common model organisms and/or industrial hosts.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: His
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bing Xia
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This his tag can be fused to the N terminus of a protein. ---- This part is in BBb Format. It is flanked by BamHI and BglII sites instead of XbaI and SpeI. More information about the BBb Format is available at:
[http://openwetware.org/wiki/Template:AndersonLab:BBb_Standard BBb Standard Description Page]

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: 7x His
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a 6x His tag head domain designed to encode the N-terminus of a protein. His tags are a type of affinity tag that can be used to purify and/or measure the quantity of proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Both Histidine codons were used to minimize repeats. An ATG start codon was used.
